The baht is issued in denominations of 10, 20, 50, 100, 500 and 1,000. Foreign currency can be exchanged at most banks, particularly central banks as well as with many money changers and exchange kiosks located at airports, shopping centers and some hotels. Credit card theft is a problem in the country so those using credit or debit cards for transfers or purchases should take care to ensure that they are not being overcharged. About US Dollar (USD)The privately owned and government sanctioned United States Federal Reserve Bank manages the monetary policy for the United States dollar (USD). The USD is the the worlds most widely held reserve currency and the most traded currency in world currency trading markets.
